<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-420] maintain HW correctly with only 1 replica in ISR</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-420</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the HW maintenance logic is only triggered when handling fetch requests from the follower. As a result, if the ISR has only 1 replica, the HW won&apos;t be incremented since there is no request from the follower to trigger the maintenance logic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
